Investigating spatial dynamics for M0 during 4.5-0Ma ( @fig-space-M0-though_time A-D) shows that mean occupancy increases with dispersal, while changes leave scale signatures and show that proportional change (i.e. $\frac{(increase - decrease)}{total\space occupancy}$). decreases with competition, while neutral models have higher proportional increase/decrease ratio. Moreover, we can see that this signature was stronger during the dynamic stage of this simulations ( @fig-space-M0-though_time I-L).

